1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 3451 By: Wilk
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Turnpike Authority;
amending 69 O.S. 2021, Section 1705, as amended by
8 Section 572, Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025 (69 O.S. Supp.
2025, Section 1705), which relates to powers and
9 duties of the Oklahoma Turnpike Authority; modifying
statutory references; modifying locations of
10 construction and operation of certain turnpikes;
requiring publication of certain notice; detailing
11 publishing requirements; requiring certain meeting be
held; requiring submission of certain report;
12 requiring report be published to website; requiring
certain formal public meeting be held; detailing
13 contents of meeting; requiring notice of certain
public meeting; detailing publishment requirements;
14 stating requirements for meeting venue; authorizing
persons to present at meeting; requiring public
15 comments be collected; requiring certain report be
submitted; requiring route changes be electronically
16 submitted; authorizing additional meetings at
Authority's discretion; requiring Authority submit
17 certain electronic report prior to completion of
design of a new route of an authorized turnpike
18 project; requiring certain authorizations terminate
after five years under certain conditions; removing
19 certain requirement for automatic tollgates;
modifying statutory references to certain proposed
20 turnpikes; requiring compensation for certain damaged
property; modifying certain entities Authority shall
21 comply with; requiring Authority adopt certain rules
and adhere to existing laws; and providing an
22 effective date.
23
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
Req. No. 14141 Page 1

1 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 69 O.S. 2021, Section 1705, as
2 amended by Section 572, Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025 (69 O.S. Supp.
3 2025, Section 1705), is amended to read as follows:
4 Section 1705. The Oklahoma Turnpike Authority is hereby
5 authorized and empowered:
6 (a) To adopt bylaws for the regulation of its affairs and
7 conduct of its business.
8 (b) To adopt an official seal and alter the same at pleasure.
9 (c) To maintain an office at such place or places within the
10 state as it may designate.
11 (d) To sue and be sued in contract, reverse condemnation,
12 equity, mandamus and similar actions in its own name, plead and be
13 impleaded; provided, that any and all actions at law or in equity
14 against the Authority shall be brought in the county in which the
15 principal office of the Authority shall be located, or in the county
16 of the residence of the plaintiff, or the county where the cause of
17 action arose. All privileges granted to the Authority and duties
18 enjoined upon the Authority by the provisions of Sections 1701
19 through 1734 1736 of this title may be enforced in a court of
20 competent jurisdiction in an action in mandamus.
21 (e) To construct, maintain, repair and operate turnpike
22 projects and highways, with their access and connecting roads, at
23 such locations and on such routes as it shall determine to be
24 feasible and economically sound; provided, that until specifically
Req. No. 14141 Page 2

