9 The Authority shall publish a notice in a newspaper of general
10 circulation in the vicinity of an authorized turnpike project that
11 states that the Authority is seeking to commence project design on
12 the route. Such notice shall be published prior to seeking any
13 contract for the design of a new route of an authorized turnpike
14 project. Such notice shall be published for four (4) consecutive
15 weeks. The Authority shall also publish and maintain such notice on
16 its website for no less than four (4) consecutive weeks.
17 The Authority's approval of any contract to undertake the design
18 of a new route of an authorized turnpike project shall take place in
19 an open and public meeting held in compliance with the Oklahoma Open
20 Meeting Act. After such meeting, the Authority shall:
21 (A) Within ninety (90) days, submit a report electronically to
22 the Governor, the members of the Legislature, and to the elected
23 officials of any city or county where the new route shall be
24 located, inclusive of conceptual project maps and preliminary
Req. No. 14141 Page 9

1 proj ect details. Such report shall also be published on the website
2 of the Authority,
3 (B) Within one hundred twenty (120) days, schedule and hold a
4 formal public meeting to provide a description of the new route and
5 preliminary project details, including the approximate location,
6 scope of work, and design elements.
7 (i) Notice of the public meeting shall be given electronically
8 by posting on the Authority's official website and by publication in
9 a newspaper of general circulation in the county where the new
10 route, or a major part of it, is to be located. The notice to be
11 published in a newspaper of general circulation shall be published
12 in four consecutive weekly issues of the newspaper, with the first
13 publication to be at least thirty (30) days prior to the public
14 meeting date. In addition to such notices, the Authority shall make
15 a good-faith effort to provide notice to all known property owners
16 within one-half (1/2) mile on each side of the new route. The
17 Authority shall use its discretion in selecting the method to
18 provide the notice to property owners, considering the number and
19 types of property interests of such owners.
20 (ii) The public meeting shall be held at a convenient location
21 that is as near to the new route as practical.
22 (iii) At the public meeting, any person may submit oral or
23 written statements and data about the new route. Reasonable limits
24 may be set upon the time allowed for oral statements.
Req. No. 14141 Page 10

1 (iv) The Authority shall also collect public comments through
2 an online portal with links to the portal shared at the public
3 meeting and on the website of the Authority. Such online portal
4 shall be open for use by the public thirty (30) days prior to the
5 public meeting,
6 (C) Within thirty (30) days of the public meeting, provide an
7 electronic report to the Governor, the Legislature, and the
8 Transportation Commission summarizing the oral and written
9 statements presented at the meeting, in addition to any data
10 received, including any economic impact reports and support or
11 opposition to a route offered by cities and counties where the new
12 route is to be located, and
13 (D) If the location of a new route changes based on the results
14 of the public meeting provided for in division (C) of this
15 subparagraph, electronically report such changes to the Governor,
16 the Legislature, the Transportation Commission, and to the elected
17 officials of cities and counties where the new route will be
18 located. Additional public meetings, conducted in accordance with
19 the provisions of division (C) of this subparagraph, may be
20 scheduled at the Authority's discretion.
21 Prior to the completion of the design of a new route of an
22 authorized turnpike project, the Authority shall electronically
23 submit to the Governor, the Legislature, and to the elected
24 officials of cities and counties where the new route will be
Req. No. 14141 Page 11

1 loca ted, the independent approval of the Transportation Commission
2 as provided in Section 1701 of this title.
3 Legislative authorization for any new turnpike location enacted
4 after the effective date of this act, shall terminate five (5) years
5 after the effective date of the act authorizing such turnpike,
6 unless the Authority has, in an open and public meeting held in
7 compliance with the Oklahoma Open Meeting Act, approved a contract
8 to commence project design.
9 All access roads, interchanges, or lead roads connecting such
10 turnpikes with existing highways must be built by funds furnished by
11 the Authority.
12 The minimum and maximum wages for the construction of the roads,
13 highways and projects provided for in Sections 1701 through 1734
14 1736 of this title shall be in accordance with the schedules of
15 wages used or adopted by the Commission in construction of state
16 highways.
17 The Authority is hereby authorized to enter into contracts or
18 agreements with agencies and instrumentalities of other states or
19 the national government for construction, maintenance and operation
20 of interstate turnpikes or highways.
21 The Authority is hereby required to construct and install
22 automatic tollgates on the Will Rogers Turnpike at State Highway No.
23 28 near Adair.
