1 (f) To issue turnpike revenue bonds of the Authority, payable
2 solely from revenues, including the revenues accruing to the trust
3 fund created by Sections 1701 through 1734 of this title, for the
4 purpose of paying all or any part of the cost of any one or more
5 turnpike projects. Provided that any bonds issued for the
6 construction of the proposed turnpike referred to in subparagraphs
7 (10) (7), (20) (8), (21) (9), and (22) (10) of paragraph (e) of this
8 section shall be issued as one issue for all four of the proposed
9 turnpikes and shall be financed, constructed and operated under one
10 bond indenture.
11 (g) To fix and revise from time to time tolls for the use of
12 any turnpike projects.
13 Any common carrier having authority at the time of opening any
14 turnpike project to operate upon a highway approximately paralleling
15 the turnpike project shall be granted without further showing
16 authority to operate over the turnpike project to all municipalities
17 which such carrier is serving at the time the turnpike project is
18 opened to traffic. But nothing herein shall be construed as
19 granting any new operation rights to any common carriers.
20 (h) To acquire, hold, and dispose of real and personal property
21 in the exercise of its powers and the performance of its duties.
22 (i) To acquire in the name of the Authority by purchase or
23 otherwise on such terms and conditions and in such manner as it may
24 deem proper, or by exercise of the right of condemnation in manner
Req. No. 14141 Page 13

1 here inafter provided, such public or private lands, including public
2 parks, playgrounds, or reservations, or parts thereof or rights
3 therein, rights-of-way, property, rights, easements, and interests,
4 as it may deem necessary for carrying out the provisions of Sections
5 1701 through 1734 1736 of this title; provided, that all public or
6 private property damaged in carrying out the powers granted by
7 Sections 1701 through 1734 1736 of this title shall be restored or
8 repaired and placed in its original condition as nearly as
9 practicable and the owner of such property be compensated in
10 accordance with the provisions of Sections 1706 through 1708 of this
11 title.
12 (j) To designate, except as is provided for herein, the
13 location, and establish, limit, and control such points of ingress
14 to and egress from each turnpike project as may be necessary or
15 desirable in the judgment of the Authority to insure the proper
16 operation and maintenance of such project, and to prohibit entrance
17 to such project from any point or points not so designated.
18 (k) To make and enter into all contracts and agreements
19 necessary or incidental to the performance of its duties and the
20 execution of its powers, and to employ consulting engineers,
21 attorneys, accountants, construction and financial experts,
22 superintendents, managers, and such other employees and agents as
